Pan African May Produce 5 Million Tons of Coal, l’Express Says

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-10-19T14:33:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-19/pan-african-may-produce-5-million-tons-of-coal-l-express-says.html
Pan African Mining Corp., an
explorer of metals, gemstones and coal in  Madagascar , expects to
produce 3 million to 5 million metric tons of coal a year in the
west of the island,  l’Express de Madagascar  reported, citing
spokesman Herindrainy Olivier Rakotomalala.  Output may reach 10 million tons a year at peak production,
the newspaper said on its  website . Pan African Mining Sakoa Coal
SA, a unit of the company, is one of five coal producers in the
Sakoa region, the newspaper said. Western Madagascar may hold as
much as 3 billion tons of coal reserves, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in  Port Louis , via the Johannesburg newsroom
at   gbell16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  